<subSubSection pageId="14" pageNumber="49" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="14.[136,1089,972,1167]" pageId="14" pageNumber="49">
Taxonomic notes. This species is allied to the former one according to its external look and genital capsule. However, the bristles of the saccular processes are on both sides reduced. The configuration of the vesica is rather different, simply retroflexed dorsally with strong sclerotisation on the inner side and with a centrally positioned stripe of fasciculate cornuti. This species is known from W 
<collectingCountry box="[359,434,1140,1166]" name="China" pageId="14" pageNumber="49">China</collectingCountry>
(
<collectingRegion box="[449,551,1140,1166]" country="China" name="Yunnan" pageId="14" pageNumber="49">Yunnan</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion box="[563,663,1140,1167]" country="China" name="Sichuan" pageId="14" pageNumber="49">Sichuan</collectingRegion>
) only and seems to be rather rare.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
